Pre-Game Insights: Cape Verde are seeking to win two consecutive matches in this qualifying campaign, while Botswana are aiming to claim their first points.
The upcoming matches against Botswana, the first encounters between the two nations, will be crucial in determining the final standings within the group.

Cape Verde have demonstrated defensive resilience in recent games, keeping six clean sheets in their last eight matches across all competitions, and they have also been formidable at home, remaining unbeaten in their last five matches, winning four and drawing one.
Others: Didier Gomes Da Rosa's men lost their first two matches in the qualifying campaign, losing 1-0 to Mauritania and 4-0 to Egypt.
Botswana have failed to score in seven of 12 matches under the French coach, while they have conceded 14 times in that period.
